M|rules|title: Hoist Static JSX Elements
M|rules|impact: LOW
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids re-creation
M|rules|tags: rendering, jsx, static, optimization
M|rules|Extract static JSX outside components to avoid re-creation.
M|rules|**Incorrect (recreates element every render):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function LoadingSkeleton() {
M|rules|return <div className="animate-pulse h-20 bg-gray-200" />
M|rules|}
M|rules|function Container() {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<div>
M|rules|{loading && <LoadingSkeleton />}
M|rules|</div>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (reuses same element):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|const loadingSkeleton = (
M|rules|<div className="animate-pulse h-20 bg-gray-200" />
M|rules|)
M|rules|function Container() {
M|rules|return (
M|rules|<div>
M|rules|{loading && loadingSkeleton}
M|rules|</div>
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|This is especially helpful for large and static SVG nodes, which can be expensive to recreate on every render.
M|rules|**Note:** If your project has [React Compiler](https://react.dev/learn/react-compiler) enabled, the compiler automatically hoists static JSX elements and optimizes component re-renders, making manual 